<p><strong>The Virgin Suicides by Jeffrey Eugenides PDF</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is the setting of "The Virgin Suicides"?</strong></p>
<p>The novel is set in Grosse Pointe, Michigan, a wealthy suburb of Detroit, in the early 1970s.</p>
<p><strong>2. Who are the main characters in "The Virgin Suicides"?</strong></p>
<p>The main characters are the Lisbon sisters, five teenage girls who commit suicide over the course of the novel. The story is narrated by a group of boys who live in the neighborhood and are obsessed with the sisters.</p>
<p><strong>3. What is the cause of the Lisbon sisters' suicides?</strong></p>
<p>The novel does not provide a definitive answer to this question. However, it suggests that the sisters are victims of their own repression and the expectations placed upon them by their parents and society.</p>
<p><strong>4. How does the novel explore the themes of adolescence and loss?</strong></p>
<p>The novel provides a poignant exploration of the confusion and pain of adolescence. The suicides of the Lisbon sisters leave a lasting impact on the boys who narrate the story, and it forces them to confront their own mortality and the fragility of life.</p>
